dialogueText.dialogue:
 Take care you tell me the Truth then;
for here's my little Finger that knows all, will tell me
if you lye.

 Ay, marry, no body can be more so; from
the Moment I saw you, I felt an Inclination for you;
I saw something of Ingenuity --

 No, no, by your Manner and Disguise, you
must needs be Squire Looby , whom we are in quest of;
let's away with him to Newgate .

 Ah! dear Sir, don't speak so of my Lady;
she's a Woman that no body can say any thing against;
a Woman without the least Grain of Artifice or 
Design, and loves my Master -- there's no saying how
much she loves him.
